      "content": "thanks for that. so i noticed the school's explanation makes it sound like this is just about being \"inclusive\" and \"supporting well-being,\" which sounds pretty straightforward. but i've been seeing a lot of other parents online saying this is actually quite controversial and goes against what they want for their kids. do you think the school is being fair in how they're presenting this, or are they leaving out why some people are actually upset?",
